{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Line a baking sheet with parchment and set aside.","Place onions, celery, garlic, parsley, sage, salt, pepper and oil into mixing bowl and chop <b>3 sec\/speed 5<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula. Place simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid and sauté <b>5 min\/250°F\/speed 0.5<b>.","Add turkey and mashed potatoes, insert measuring cup and mix <b>10 sec\/\/speed 4<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside until cool enough to handle (approx. 10 min.).","Crack eggs into a bowl and whisk lightly with a fork. Set aside.","Place a separate bowl onto mixing bowl lid, weigh in bread crumbs and set aside.","Once reserved turkey mixture is cool enough to handle, divide and shape into oval patties (approx. 1 oz ea.) (see Tip). Refrigerate 10 minutes.","Dip chilled patties into egg mixture then coat in bread crumbs. Transfer to prepared baking sheet.","Heat oil to fry in a small pot over medium heat (see Tip).","Fry croquettes in small batches until golden brown (approx. 2 min. per batch). Transfer to paper towels to drain. Allow to cool slightly, garnish with chopped fresh parsley and serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["4 oz yellow onions, in pieces","2 oz celery, in pieces","2 garlic cloves","5 sprigs fresh parsley, leaves only, plus extra to garnish","½ tsp dried sage","½ tsp salt","¼ tsp ground black pepper","1 tbsp olive oil","8 oz cooked turkey meat","10 oz mashed potatoes","3 large eggs","4 oz bread crumbs","neutral oil, to fry"]}],"id":"r417502","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-kXNcwu1_AnQ\/XZMuQO8lrNI\/AAAAAAAAaDE\/cmP5SKfCQ_gX-gx7XWMhVJJ4X_49Eey2ACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_Efdhys7UsuXofDJz.png","title":"Turkey and Mashed Potato Croquettes","publishedAt":"2018-11-16T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"5 g","fat":"2 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"6 g","calories":"247 kJ \/ 59 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking sheet, parchment paper, saucepot, paper towels, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["If mixture is too soft to shape, add an additional 2 tbsp of bread crumbs.","Serve with cranberry sauce or gravy.","For crispy, golden results: use a thermometer to ensure oil temperature is maintained between 350°F-375°F."],"basicInfo":["easy","30m","55m","22 pieces"]}